items.title: Ask HN: Is all AI coded code in the public domain?
items.summary: AFAIK it's generally assumed (but not(?) tested in court, that LLMs can't be assigned copyright, and that copyright for work generated by LLMs can't be claimed by a human just for being in the loop. Is there going to be an avalanche of code that is legally in the public domain, going forward? Comments URL: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=46063586 Points: 4 # Comments: 4
